my friend is having a mental breakdown what do i do she found an old picture of her grandfather and heard a song he once sung to her to get her to go to sleep at a reasonable hour when she was a kid she was only ten when he died and it was five days after her tenth birthday he was her hero when you saw him more than likely you saw her she goes into these moods every year twice a year sept th and dec th his birthday and the day he died she always scream that she hates him for what he did to their family his death tore the family apart she screams that she hates that he took the first drink and that first ciregret but the thing is she was just fine until she heard that song and started to sing along with it what do i do she is the sweetest girl i know she never shows her true feelings in public she goes to his gravesite twice a year and puts flowers down and sing a song or recite her lastest poem she talks to him and then saids goodbye again and come back to town every time she does she gives her friends and family a hug and tells them she loves them she hangs on closer to her mom and dad and the only other grandparents she has now tighter she does the same thing with me why does she relive that day all over agian year after year its hard for me to see her do this she has seen professionals and they cant do any more for her thats the only reason she hasnt killed herself yet the professionals helped her through the suiciedal part of her depression but she just busted out crying one day in church we were talking about cancer and all that and she just got up and ran from the room i followed her and so did the youth pastor i asked her what was wrong and she couldnt speak because of the tears and her crying i looked at the youth minstor and put my arms around her and took her outside that time she cried so much she made herself sick it hurt me that was during the time me and her were boyfriend and girlfriend when she goes through this she wont let anyone touch her im scared that the suiciedal toughts are coming back up everytime she goes through this what you've described is not a mental breakdown your friend is having what is actually a very common grief reaction many people become very sad every year on the anniversary of a terrible loss i will say though that it sounds like your friend's grief is not a healthy type of grief sometimes when the loss of a loved one is especially traumatic the surviving loved ones can become stuck in grief while this is not all that uncommon it's not healthy for your friend's sake you should gently encourage her to see a therapist to see if she can learn to resolve her grief but if you can't get her to do this then just be there for her to listen when she's struggling and know that these spells will pass Shaggy dog story Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Grief Pitaten Friends Sin City EastEnders Avenue Q Kodocha Time Out of Mind Scenes from a Memory Drawn Together Garfield Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Marilyn Monroe Humphrey Bogart Theory of conduct W.I.T.C.H. Ron and Fez Social rule The Catcher in the Rye Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Le Malade imaginaire The Invisibles Jon Secada One Tree Hill (TV series) The Curse of Fenric Days of our Lives Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Characters in the Smurfs Kurt Cobain She Loves You Phoebe Buffay's songs Dead Like Me About a Boy Cindy Sheehan Babe Ruth Everwood Blood on the Tracks Rent (musical) Recurring South Park characters YuYu Hakusho 50 First Dates Boston Public The Smoking Room Hey Jude Charly Garc__a The Jim Rome Show Cardcaptor Sakura The Inside Sant Thakar Singh Good Morning, Vietnam The Shining (film) Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist The Adventures of Pete & Pete Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban The Human Stain The Emancipation of Mimi Salad Fingers The Ashlee Simpson Show Miss Saigon Jewish bereavement Mojave people South Park RuneScape quests Great Teacher Onizuka Night (book) Episodes of Lost (Season 2) Blonde on 